and because of these issues most talked in
the international level

241
00:13:35,889 --> 00:13:37,870
and they would say "oh, it's nothing.

242
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:40,529
We don't really interfere Burma"

243
00:13:40,529 --> 00:13:41,529
but on the other hand,

244
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:44,480
they are supporting in many different ways
to make sure

245
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,830
that there's conflict.

246
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:53,649
So China would come up with things based on
their interests.

247
00:13:53,649 --> 00:13:56,850
So speaking of China's interest in Burma,

248
00:13:56,850 --> 00:13:57,899
China has this one belt,

249
00:13:57,899 --> 00:14:01,050
one road plan where they're investing in a
lot of countries

250
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:05,060
and I know with Burma, they have the China-Myanmar
Economic Corridor

251
00:14:05,060 --> 00:14:08,250
which is part of the belt and road.

252
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:10,760
What are they investing in in Burma?

253
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:14,740
So most of the extractive industry like jade,
or amber, or gold,

254
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:21,180
they are mostly influenced by the Chinese
businesses

255
00:14:21,180 --> 00:14:25,339
and then now they are trying to push for

256
00:14:25,339 --> 00:14:30,199
one of the biggest hydropower dam in northern
Burma

